  "prompt": "Has Mohammed married his daughter?",
  "response": "No, Muhammad, the prophet of Islam, did not marry his daughter. Muhammad had several wives, but he did not marry any of his own children. His daughters were:\n\n1. Zainab bint Muhammad\n2. Ruqayyah bint Muhammad\n3. Umm Kulthum bint Muhammad\n4. Fatimah bint Muhammad\n\nNone of his daughters were married to him; they were married to other individuals. For example, Fatimah, his youngest daughter, was married to Ali ibn Abi Talib, who was Muhammad's cousin and one of his closest companions.",
